Introduction

DB 
.digital system for data arrangement and storage 
.facilitates efficient management of data
    .enables addition, modification, removal, and access of info

MySQL 
.open-source RDBMS that uses SQL to manage data 
.reliable, fast, and easy to use 
.allows creation, modification, and maintenance of databases 
.provides multiple features:
    .data storage - efficiently store large amounts of data 
    .data retrieval - allows quick and easy access to data 
    .data manipulation - supports ops like inserting, updating, etc 
    .data security - offers robust security features to protect data 
    .scalability - can handle small to large applications with ease 

MySQL Query
.act as instructions 
    .receive specific data
    .fiter results
    .perform calculations 

.select 
.retrieves info and stores it in a table (result set)
.allows column specification for data retrieval, and can apply filters to only get the data that meets specific conditions
.uses various clauses: 
    .select - specifies the columns or expressions to retrieve from the DB table 
    .from - indicates the table from which to fetch the data
    .where - optional clause allowing me to specify conditions to filter the rows retrieved from the table
        .only rows that satisfy the condition will be included in the result set 
    .order by - optional clause used to sort the result set in ascending or descending order based on one or more columns
    .limit - optional clause that restricts the number of rows returned by the query
        .useful when only wanting to retrieve a certain number of rows from the result set 

